  </style>

  <div class="dcf-wrapper">
    <div class="header">
      <div class="header-content">
        <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
        <h1>Northrop Grumman (NOC)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Northrop Grumman. Using mathematically derived growth and discount rates to find a single intrinsic value number.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      {intrinsicValuePerShare !== null ? (
        <>
          <div class="verdict-card">
            <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
            <div class="verdict-price">${intrinsicValuePerShare.toFixed(2)}</div>
            <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice?.toFixed(2) ?? 'N/A'} ({marginOfSafety?.toFixed(1) ?? 'N/A'}%)</div>
            <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
              {verdictText}
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="stats-row">
            <div class="stat-card">
              <div class="stat-value">${data.revenueHistory.length > 0 ? (data.revenueHistory[0] / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B</div>
              <div class="stat-label">Latest Revenue</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
              <div class="stat-value">${fcfLatest !== null ? (fcfLatest / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B</div>
              <div class="stat-label">Latest FCF</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
              <div class="stat-value">${data.epsHistory.length > 0 ? data.epsHistory[0].toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
              <div class="stat-label">Latest EPS</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
              <div class="stat-value">{sharesOutstanding !== null ? sharesOutstanding : 'N/A'}M</div>
              <div class="stat-label">Shares Out.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
              <div class="stat-value">${netCash !== null ? (netCash / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B</div>
              <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
          <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model to calculate the intrinsic value of Northrop Grumman (NOC).</p>

          <div class="method-step">
            <div class="step-num">1</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
              <p>We anchor our valuation using the most recently reported annual Free Cash Flow of <strong>${fcfLatest !== null ? (fcfLatest / 1000).toFixed(2) : 'N/A'} billion</strong>, ensuring we rely on mathematically verified, hard cash generated by the business rather than accounting earnings.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="method-step">
            <div class="step-num">2</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
              <p>We apply a mathematically derived growth rate to project cash flows for the next 5 years. This phase accounts for near-term momentum and current defense budget realities.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="method-step">
            <div class="step-num">3</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
              <p>After Year 5, we assume the company enters a mature state, growing at a modest, perpetual rate (the Gordon Growth Model). This captures all value from Year 6 to infinity.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="method-step">
            <div class="step-num">4</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
              <p>We discount future cash flows back to today using a discount rate (WACC) that reflects the opportunity cost of capital, grounded by the current 10Y Treasury yield (4.18%) plus an equity risk premium.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="method-step">
            <div class="step-num">5</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
              <p>Enterprise Value plus Net Cash equals Equity Value. We divide this by the outstanding share count ({sharesOutstanding}M) to arrive at the intrinsic value per share.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2>The Three Core Assumptions</h2>
          <p>Our model is driven by exactly three mathematically derived assumptions. No multiples or fabrications—just the data.</p>

          <div class="assumption-grid">
            <div class="assumption-card">
              <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
              <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
              <div class="rationale">
                Based on historical multi-year revenue CAGR calculations from scraped data. We established a baseline growth rate that reflects Northrop Grumman's steady defense contract revenue streams without over-extrapolating transient surges.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="assumption-card">
              <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
              <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
              <div class="rationale">
