          <h2>Risks to This Valuation</h2>
          <h3>Upside Risks (Why it might be worth more)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Geopolitical Escalation:</strong> Increased global tensions or direct conflicts could lead to emergency defense spending bills, immediately boosting NOC's backlog and revenue growth beyond our 5% baseline.</li>
            <li><strong>Space Systems Outperformance:</strong> NOC is heavily invested in space systems. Outsized success in winning highly classified, lucrative space-based defense contracts could rapidly expand operating margins and FCF.</li>
            <li><strong>B-21 Raider Scaling:</strong> As the B-21 stealth bomber program transitions from low-rate initial production to full-scale deployment, economies of scale could yield higher profitability than currently modeled.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Downside Risks (Why it might be worth less)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>U.S. Budget Constraints:</strong> Political gridlock or a shift toward fiscal austerity in Washington could lead to defense budget freezes or cuts, stunting top-line growth.</li>
            <li><strong>Fixed-Price Contract Overruns:</strong> Defense contractors often face significant margin compression or outright losses on fixed-price development contracts if technological hurdles cause delays and cost overruns.</li>
            <li><strong>Supply Chain Fragility:</strong> Ongoing bottlenecks in acquiring specialized microelectronics, raw materials, or skilled labor could delay revenue recognition and compress FCF margins.</li>
          </ul>

